3:[["$","h2",null,{"children":"What Is a Cold Air Intake and Why Does It Matter?"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["A cold air intake relocates your engine's air filter away from the hot engine bay and replaces the restrictive factory airbox with a smoother, larger-diameter tube. The result: ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"denser, cooler air"}]," reaches the combustion chamber, producing more power with every stroke."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Stock intake systems are designed around noise, cost, and emissions — not performance. Swapping to a cold air intake is one of the fastest ways to free up hidden horsepower your engine already has."}],"\n",["$","h3",null,{"children":"How Much Power Can You Expect?"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Gains vary by platform, but real-world dyno pulls typically show:"}],"\n",["$","ul",null,{"children":["\n",["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"5–15 whp"}]," on naturally aspirated engines"]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"10–25 whp"}]," on forced-induction builds (where airflow is even more critical)"]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"Noticeable improvement in throttle response and induction sound"}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","hr",null,{}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"children":"Top Cold Air Intakes of 2024"}],"\n",["$","h3",null,{"children":"1. K&N 69-Series Typhoon"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"The K&N Typhoon is the benchmark for bolt-on cold air intakes. The washable, oiled cotton-gauze filter flows 50% more air than a paper stock filter, and the mandrel-bent aluminum tube minimizes turbulence."}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Best for:"}]," Daily drivers wanting reliability and proven gains\n",["$","strong",null,{"children":"Avg. gain:"}]," 8–12 whp\n",["$","strong",null,{"children":"Price:"}]," $280–$350"]}],"\n",["$","h3",null,{"children":"2. Injen SP Series Short Ram / Cold Air Combo"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Injen's SP series uses a patented MR Technology heat shield to isolate the intake from engine heat. The polished stainless finish is a showroom favorite, and the included dry-flow filter never needs oiling."}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Best for:"}]," Enthusiasts who want low maintenance\n",["$","strong",null,{"children":"Avg. gain:"}]," 6–10 whp\n",["$","strong",null,{"children":"Price:"}]," $220–$310"]}],"\n",["$","h3",null,{"children":"3. AEM 21-Series Cold Air Intake"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"AEM targets serious performance enthusiasts. The large-diameter inlet tube is 10% wider than most competitors, and the Dryflow filter is washable without oil — eliminating risk of MAF sensor contamination."}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Best for:"}]," Track builds and aggressive street use\n",["$","strong",null,{"children":"Avg. gain:"}]," 10–18 whp\n",["$","strong",null,{"children":"Price:"}]," $300–$380"]}],"\n",["$","h3",null,{"children":"4. Mishimoto Performance Air Intake"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["Mishimoto's offering stands out with a ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"lifetime warranty"}]," and the cleanest engineering in this price bracket. The heat shield is double-walled for superior thermal insulation."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Best for:"}]," Long-term ownership and warranty peace of mind\n",["$","strong",null,{"children":"Avg. gain:"}]," 7–13 whp\n",["$","strong",null,{"children":"Price:"}]," $250–$330"]}],"\n",["$","hr",null,{}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"children":"Installation Tips"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["Installing a cold air intake is typically a ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"1–2 hour DIY job"}]," requiring only basic hand tools. Follow these steps for a clean install:"]}],"\n",["$","ol",null,{"children":["\n",["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Disconnect the battery"}]," before touching any electrical connections near the intake"]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"Remove the factory airbox and all attached ducting"}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":["Unplug the ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"MAF sensor"}]," carefully — this is your most expensive component"]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"Route the new intake tube following the included template"}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":["Secure all clamps to ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"4–5 Nm"}]," — over-tightening cracks silicone couplers"]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"children":"Clear any fault codes and let the ECU relearn with a 20-minute drive cycle"}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","blockquote",null,{"children":["\n",["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Pro tip:"}]," After installation, always check for vacuum leaks by listening for a whistling sound at idle. A cheap smoke tester removes all doubt."]}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","hr",null,{}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"children":"Oiled vs. Dry Filter: Which Should You Choose?"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"| Feature | Oiled Filter | Dry Filter |\n|---|---|---|\n| Filtration | Excellent | Very good |\n| Airflow | Slightly higher | Slightly lower |\n| Maintenance | Re-oil every 30k mi | Wash only |\n| MAF safety | Risk if over-oiled | No risk |"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["For most street builds, ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"dry filters win on convenience"}],". For maximum filtration on dusty roads or track environments, oiled filters remain the gold standard."]}],"\n",["$","hr",null,{}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"children":"Conclusion"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"A cold air intake remains one of the best bang-for-buck modifications available. For under $350, you get real, measurable power gains, improved throttle response, and an aggressive induction sound that makes every drive more engaging."}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":"Start with a quality unit from K&N, AEM, or Injen — all three offer platform-specific kits with guaranteed fitment and dyno-proven results."}]]
